title: Grateful Dead Live at Freedom Hall on 1993-06-15
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Althea, Wang Dang Doodle, Friend Of The Devil, Desolation Row, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Victim Or The Crime, Crazy Fingers-> Estimated Prophet-> Spoonful-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> Morning Dew, E: Gloria

reviews.review_text:
Finally a 93 I can listen to 93' was a strange year for soundboards. Healy put the amps under the stage and stage monitors had vanished in favor of in ears. The kick drum mic was bad all year and Healy was too baked to troubleshoot it so all the pure boards have a strange popping from Billy's kick. 

Many matrices have phase issues. This one sounds good to my ears. What guitar was Jerry using here? It sounds like wolf. Lightning bolt made it's debut Eugene 93 in Aug but I though he had brought wolf back for a bit. 

Weir screws Wang Dang lyrics up. 

Jerry seems lucid.
Thank you! Just a note of thanks for choosing my B&K pull for the matrix, it came out really nice!
